76561197969454892,Recommended,314230,32067261,Posted: 30 May,all,Inignot12,"One guy, just one developer has been tirelessly and consistantly working on this gem for several years now.  I've had it since it was first on early access and I'm astonished at how far the game has come.  The developer (again 1 GUY!) is constantly putting out more content and updates at a rate that would make full studios blush.The game itself is an atmospheric masterpiece.  It is a labor of love to bring one man's vision to life of these alien worlds.  Yes, the alien worlds are not complete ecosystems, but they need not be.  They each have their own felling that is embelleshed by the different colors of sunrises/sunsets, the AMAZING music that each planet has as its theme.It is well worth the asking price, and I hope one day to see a completed release.  Even in it's current state, it's one of the better examples of Early Access developments on steam, period."
