76561198064474628,Recommended,314230,32751248,Posted: 24 June,all,Silver,"This game is wonderful. The developer made so many smart design decisions. The music enhances the gameplay experience and sets a tone of adventure, wonder, and potential danger. The design of the ship is charming and believable, as it originally had a sizeable crew. And the holographic viewscreen design is gorgeous.The tutorials and explanations are very clear, although initially I didn't understand that the ship had default weapons other than missiles I picked up as this wasn't indicated but it's a minor oversight. I also enjoy that the ship's health regenerates after not taking damage for a time. This signalled to me that the game would focus more on adventure and exploration rather than wasting the player's time gathering resources, like in many other open world exploration games.The ship to ship combat is fun and intuitive and I also liked the fps combat. Fighting in a low gravity environment with a deep space background against multiple jumping enemies reminded me of some of the best parts of unreal tournament (in terms of the atmosphere; I don't mean to imply the gunplay is as nuanced as a more narrowly-focused fps would be expected to be). Also, the writing seems solid thus far. Each entry doesn't read as being from the same voice, even if it was written by the same author, which is a plus for immersion.I recommend this game to anyone who is interested in a fun and easy to get into sci-fi/space exploration game with great atmosphere and honestly fun gameplay."
