76561198057921326,Recommended,314230,14400011,"Posted: 9 February, 2015",all,jedison96,"Though a bit on the low-res type for a game of its kind, it's fantastic! It allows seamless space travel between different planets in a star system. Not only that, but the soundtrack is procedural depending on the different actions you do. For instance: Just this morning, i was going towards a planet, when all of a sudden BOOM! The music changed because i was entering the atmosphere. Another thing: the realistic physics play a very important part in this game's playability. You don't just fly from Point A to Point B. You actually have to use your thrusters in different stages to prevent burning in the atmosphere, crashing into the planet, and being blown up by enemies. Not only that, but your hull can get damaged, causing fires, leaking oxygen, and worse. This game is especially useful for it's compatibility. I'm playing on a 5 year old laptop with crappy graphics, and it still has intricate detail! One last bit of information you should know: it has a story line as well as open world. It has good potential and should continue to thrive!"
76561198082853422,Recommended,314230,28649393,"Posted: 25 December, 2016",all,TheZWA,"Dissapointed by No Man's Sky and need something to scratch your space exploration itch? Rodina might be the game for you.In Rodina you explore a vast solar system with 4 massive planets all roughly the size earth and tens of thousands of asteroids. You will need to scavenge items and fight off hostile xenos to uncover the storyline. The feeling of loneliness surrounds you and the amazing soundtrack enchances the feeling of solitude.The storyline is absolutely amazing even when it's purely made of text. Be prepared to read. It will keep you engaged and it will surprise you.The combat happens in air and on land. The land battles FPS battles against xenos with different kind of weaponry. The air/space battles are fought with space ships and different kind of weaponry which you can easily equip to your spaceship. My only problem with the combat is that the guns you get to currently use in land combat feel like peashooters, so it's a lot easier to just kill everyone with your spaceship.The spaceship has a fully customisable interior, which I have spent a lot of time on making it fit me. It really adds to the homeliness of the spaceship. While the exterior can't be changed in the current version in vanilla, modding the game is pretty easy so you can go download exteriors for Nexus Mods. So with mods you can fully customize the ship to your liking.There is basically only one type of thing you do to get forward in the game. Fly into a plus sign in an object, kill all enemies on the site, and salvage the items left there. It might sound lame but I have had a lot of fun with it so far, purely because the atmosphere engrosses me in the world.This game is still in early access, but it still manages to do what many other games will never achieve. Best part is... It keeps getting updated and in the coming year the game will advance a lot. I recommend looking the roadmap at the Elliptic Games site.Basically this game is worth your money in it's current state and it will only get better from now. Buy it."
