76561198042327711,Recommended,314230,18492483,"Posted: 15 October, 2015",all,PiemanFiddy,"This game is still very, very early access, but for what it's worth it's one of the few amazing early access games on the store.Basically the objective of the game is to fly around in your own customisable spaceship, around to other nearby planets to collect data, logs or an assortment of upgrades.There are also enemies littered around the planets (and even asteroids) that will attempt to kill you. The combat system can be rather tricky, but overall it's very fun.There's also a system in place that allows you to set the speed of your own ship. You have a choice between ""Docking Speed"", ""Combat Speed"", and ""Cruising Speed"". There's another speed modifier you can find via exploration called ""Limnal Speed"" which allows you to travel at, what else? Light speed!There's tons to do in this game as well. Including landing on planets/asteroids! When you're near a planet (with an atmosphere) you will begin atmospheric re-entry. This is a little 'minigame' in which you attempt to keep your ship at a proper angle and speed to avoid it being damaged by the heat. This heat can also spark fires in your ship, but don't worry! There's a handy fire extinguisher for you just in case.Once you land on a planet, exiting it is very simple. Simply point up and out. However be wary of the enemies that surround the planets in this game. They're far more common on the planets themselves instead of asteroids and WILL hunt you down!There's already tons of things to do in this game, and it's not even finished yet! I would highly recommend this game to anyone who's looking for a laid-back space exploration game. There's plenty of sandbox to go around. Just steer clear of the star."
