76561198271727425,Recommended,314230,21741111,"Posted: 9 March, 2016",all,rtd,"This is a fun game with considerable potential.Rodina definitely succeeded in making me feel like the captain of my own spaceship, going on adventures that only loosely felt like it had all been scripted by someone.The game's story is clever in content and execution.  It's clear about events yet cryptic how you fit in.  It goes at your own pace and you don't know who to trust, and is topped off with a plot twist I didn't see coming.The story is presented to you in such a way that you feel like an observer looking in, if it weren't for the fact that the game tells you you're involved, but not how.  The story isn't forced upon you, either.  You can discover it at your own pace, along with side stories, some funny, some intriguing, some dark, and some all at once.Combat never gets old.  You're flying around super fast to catch and satisfyingly shoot down aliens while avoiding their fire and defensively blasting their missiles, making you feel like a space ninja.The game has many small but really neat details.  Defeated alien ships will crash land into any nearby planet.  Entering the atmosphere will jostle the camera and surround your ship with flames until you've finally entered the atmosphere, accompanied with the perfect sound effect while fully revealing the beauty of the new world.  You can customize the interior of your ship.  You can pilot it in first or third person.  You can leave it running and walk around in your ship, and even jump out of it or open the airlock to quench flames in emergencies when your extinguishers aren't enough.There's more to this early access game, but I'm not gonna spoil any more.  Give this game a try."
76561198010177451,Recommended,314230,20945538,"Posted: 3 February, 2016",all,dessnr,"Grab a copy of this when you can if you enjoyed Elite: Crap house... Oh I mean, Elite: Dangerous.  Whilst Horizons is very pretty, where this game lacks graphics, it makes up for great game play and an addictive story.  At first you seem like it's going to be utter crap but then when you get past the initialisation, the game is only up hill from there.Corny graphics (although the planets are not that much less in detail than what we see in Elite and the game runs faster) but the game play and story are just what the doctor ordered.Developers, don't give up on this game.  It's a game that requires brains and that's why there ain't too many people playing just yet.  But don't worry, people with good minds don't take long to catch onto something good and they will pay the money.I will be buying this for a few friends and mentioning it on a show I do, to get the ball rolling.Cheers for a great game.P.S.  I love how we have to break atmo, before we can land."
,Recommended,314230,21423318,"Posted: 24 February, 2016",all,StaticCøde,"This game... this freaking amazing of a game. Rodina is a space exploration game, with enimies that you can shoot down to take over a planet. There are 4 planets (Hopefully there will be more in the future) that you can visit and land on. Although in the spaceship that you fly around in makes everything seem small, YOU'RE SO WRONG. SO SO SO WRONG. The sense of scale in this game is far past anygame that I've ever seen. Infact, the spaceship itself is about the size of a house. The mountains are gigantic, in the sense it takes 30 minutes+ to climb some of the tallest ones. You have a jetpack that lets you fly around as well, which is very fun. The game has three main modes, Normal, Freeform, and Peaceful. Normal is more or less the main story of the game, in which you can easily die. Freeform is basically the creative mode, although you can still die in it. And I haven't played peaceful, so I'm not sure what that is about. The games graphics are kind of polished-pixelated. They look amazing but can run on most computers, even if you have a potato. And you may think the ""No loading screens"" in the game description is false, IT'S NOT. The only loading screen I've ever seen in this game is the one that you get once you boot up the game, which, loads very very quickly. So, it's a very nice game, it's a little bit limited on the planets, but hopefully more will be added. This game is wroth $15. If you like Space Engineers, Space Engine, Universe Sandbox 2, or Sol 0, get this game!"
