,Recommended,314230,29864854,Posted: 11 February,all,Übermensch,"I tend to rate games on whether they provide at least 1 hour of entertainment per £. Well, given that I just reached that point, I can say that this game does.Be warned, though, it is NOT a complete game. It's the bare-bones of a game. It's playable, it's fun and it's a great teaser of what might come next, but if you're looking for a fully polished space game, this isn't it. Go and get Elite or something.Basically, you're a person who is flying round, building their ship up, killing aliens and following some vague plot threads about the state of humanity and the events preceeding the game. These threads begin to draw together and form what the game calls 'Chapter One', which I found very enticing, and which goes in a very interesting direction by the end. Presumably, I'm on Chapter Two now, which involves building a wang for a robot, but again, this is dressed in a very interesting set of threads.One of the main features that this game has over most is the ship interior editor and moddability. Say you want to have the Enterprise, you can make your interior like it, then download a model to make it look like that (I'm not actually sure if there is an Enterprise, the mod scene is small). Or if you want a little ship, you could have one room with all the stuff you need. Even though the building system is very much not complete, it's still really fun and quite powerful (and multiple levels and a better layout planner are on the cards for the future updates).All in all, if you're willing to take a punt, buy it or try the demo. If you want to hold off, you do that and wait until it's got more features. Hopefully, there will be some major updates in 2017, which looking at the dev's monthly-ish track record, looks likely."
