76561198194518690,Recommended,314230,27550787,"Posted: 25 November, 2016",all,(LAG) Niteguard,"Rodina. What a beautiful game, I simply can't understand why you would play anything else.First of all this game is set in space so it's already cool, but what is even better is your FULLY CUSTOMISABLE SPACESHIP! with that you can really get to know your ship and maybe even roleplay a bit.Then there are space enemies, meaning you can have epic space battles fighting with or against a variety of weapons. Or you could decide to take it to close combat and blast the alien fools once you've boarded their space stations.Meanwhile in this already fully immersive and incredible combat you will have some cool music playing. Music, no big deal right? Wrong. The music in this game makes it twice as better even if you're cruising around a planet, or in fast paced combat or even running around your spaceship like a madman.After all this there is more! The flying in this game is absolutely brilliant, at all times you feel very in control of what your ship is doing. (Except when you are in limnal drive.) Zoom around space at multiple speeds and really understand how BIG space is. Even at the fastest speed you're going to have trouble reaching the other end.The Planets are excellent and many aliens inhabit them. Then there are hundreds of asteroids, seriously that isnt an exageration. The asteroids also inhabited by aliens. Then as mentioned before there are alien space stations littered around space. On all planets and asteroids there is tons of loot to find including space emails that progresses the story. All planets have there own music too!The very simple art style works perfectly.This has been my review on Rodina, obviously this game is in early access at the moment and things could change but when it is finished i will look forward to playing it. At it's current state i would give it a very honest 9.5/10.-Niteguard"
,Recommended,314230,29324126,Posted: 17 January,all,CosmicSloth,"This review consists of the factors that led me to the decision of buying this game. I originally started off with the demo, and I was sold. I insist you do the same.The story and soundtrack in Rodina are supurb. Although the main story in this game isn't on par with games like Mass Effect, for a one man dev, the writing is fantastic (I'm not sure if Brendan/Raptormeat does all the writing or if he has help). Rodina's story is refreshing, in a sense that you really feel like the transmissions you read are from real people in a real universe. I've been on the edge of my seat when reading some of these. The story drew me into this ficitonal universe.The soundtrack, story, ship customization, and the sheer scale of the planets are what really drew me in. I'm a gamer that loves a good soundtrack, and this game definitely delivers.At the time of writing, I have 9 hours logged (I bought this game yesterday (1/16)); and I would say that 4 of those hours were consumed by ship customization. You have complete freedom when customizing your ship. There are mods for this game that one can download to acquire new types of ships, but I really enjoy the simplicity of the vanilla ship.As for the planets, there has been countless times where I've landed my ship, thinking I was close to my target, when in reality, I was hundred of meters off. People who have played this game know what I'm talking about. At times, it's truley hard to comprehend how massive some of these planets really are.If you're not yet convinced, try the demo. With the demo, you acquire the entire game, but are limted to 90 minutes of gameplay. If you decide to buy the game, you can start right where you left off.So start with the demo, and enjoy a truly remarkable game."
