76561197972843920,Recommended,314230,14735641,"Posted: 4 March, 2015",all,AliensOnMars,"This is a fantastic game and is full of promise.There's something quite sublime about flying to the tallest peak of a mountain range (and these moutains can be TALL) and looking out over an alien landscape watching the sky gradually lighten and the shadows fade as the planet's rotation brings it to face the system's star. Then you can simply hop into your ship aim it at the sky (perhaps at that intersting point of light you spied in the night sky) and fly into space with the backdoor open to watch those mammoth peaks retreat into the background of the planet's surface.Equally satisfying is the inertia based space flight and combat - a highlight for me was strolling around on the ground when I noticed a meteor shower landing close to me...only to realise it was the incoming fire from some dive bombing fighters, after a tense sprint back to the ship, and even tenser dogfight, watching the wreckage of the enemy ships dwindle to tiny points of flame on the vast terrain below was both oddly satisfying and reminds you of the scale of this experience you're sitting in.Finally it's worth mentioning this all occurs against a background of great music (makes me feel like I'm part of 2001 Space Odyssey) and a really excellently written (if currently background) story that you can discover as you explore.I really recommend buying this game, enjoying it and then keeping your eye on it - the developer has big goals and if you buy this now you'll not only be in for a treat but be investing in an even greater one on the horizon."
76561198062338961,Recommended,314230,17975427,"Posted: 10 September, 2015",all,mjk500,"To start off I would like to make abundantly clear this game is early in development.  There isn't much to do other than scavenge and fight enemies, but that part is well made.  Personally I enjoyed the space combat, and the holosticks you find around the solar system are very interesting.  Also I would like to add that the physics in this game are very realsitic, and the visuals are stunning, watching the sun rise on the side of a planetis beautiful, especially morena.  While there are no quests, the developer (yes there is only one) has big plans, and is active in the community.  He responds to a lot of the comments people have, and has already begun implementing some npcs in the game.  The game is very fun to load up every few days and fly around a alien solar.  It also has full controller support, and isn't broken in any way.  Some people have expierienced bugs, but I haven't.  If you enjoy exploration and space, and can stop to smell the roses that are in this game, I'm sure you'll enjoy it."
,Recommended,314230,17823544,"Posted: 31 August, 2015",all,Scionni,"Even as millions of dollars are constantly being funneled into Star Citizen's production, Cloud Imperium's proven team of engineers and artists reach for the Holy Grail of space simulation that the single developer of Rodina has already claimed. What Rodina lacks in visual polish and superficial content, it more than makes up for with a flawlessly seamless harmony between interstellar, planetary, and ship-based gameplay. Ever wanted the ability to fight hull fires in your custom made ship as it plummeted rapidly through the atmosphere of an undiscovered planet? That I know of, Rodina is the only space simulator currently with that capacity.Good - You'll get a space flight sim experienced that you've only been able to fantasize. This is what Star Citizen and Elite: Dangerous hope to be some day.Bad - The game is still in tentative development, and as such, lacks many secondary and tertiary features that ought to populate a gamespace as open and as unhindering as Rodina's. Rest assured, however, that the developer is working on truly solid foundations, and given time, Rodina will be soaked with features."
