,Recommended,314230,18979245,"Posted: 9 November, 2015",all,CaptainSiscold,"Oh...oh...my goodness. I just finished the storyline as far as it goes at the moment, and I'm just sitting here in awe. Forget any other purchases you were going to make, buy this game right now. You will not regret it.For a more in-depth review:Rodina is a retro-style space sim done in an open-world style, meaning that you can fly about an entire actual size solar system with no loading screens. It's a bit thin on features at the moment, but it's still Early Access, and in my experience has been incredibly stable for an Early Access title.Graphics/SFX: 8/10Graphics are kind of retro-styled, but still look quite good, with terrain textures being fairly detailed, ship interiors looking AWESOME, and sound effects being perfect for this type of game. However, the exterior of your ship is somewhat bland (the ship design can apparently be edited in 3D modeling programs, so if you would like, I believe this can be changed), and planet terrain mostly consists of cliffs, hills, and mountains, with no vegetation or anything to make them feel more ""real"". This is perfectly acceptable in an Early Access game imo, but it's worth noting.Soundtrack: 10/10GET THE SOUNDTRACK, TOO. I'm serious. The Rodina OST is one of the most beautiful pieces of work I've ever heard, perfectly meshing with the gameplay. Flying between asteroids? The music is nice and peaceful, capturing the awe of just staring at the beauty of the universe. Moving into combat? The music shifts to adrenaline-inducing battle music. It's a masterpiece equaled in only a handful of other games I've played. My top three game soundtracks are (in no particular order): FTL, Risk of Rain, and Rodina.Gameplay/Story: 9/10Words cannot describe it, because it's so freaking AWESOME. The only reason that it misses out on a perfect score is the fact that it's currently unfinished. The combination of listening to the awesome soundtrack while reading the incredibly emotional dialogue in the encrypted communications...beautiful.Overall: 9/10A beautiful work by a very talented developer, missing out on a perfect score only due to the unfinished nature of the game. This is the only game I've ever bought at list price, and I have zero regrets. The developer seems committed to further progress on the game, and I'm confident in wholeheartedly recommending this game. If you're considering getting it, stop considering and start buying!"
