,Recommended,314230,12190431,"Posted: 22 September, 2014",all,SirSqueembo,"I enjoy looking around the early access section of Steam to see what new games have been released, but it pain me to think that most of these game will never see the end of their development. Many of the early access games I have purchased have minimal features, extremely high performance issues and no promise of ever being finished. One of my most recent experiences with a game like this was with Next Car Game. While it was fun and has loads of promise...the updates are few and far between, and none of them have ever improved the performance of the gameRodina, however, is much different. Not only does it have a fantastic demo (a rare thing these days) but it runs like a dream. The first impression I had of this game is that the dev cares about Rodina and won't let it go like the other indie dev often do. Hell, this one guy has created a game that runs better on launch than an entire AAA development studio can do (cough cough DICE LA!)The game has released with a decent number of features and great performance that rarely drops. The randomly generated solar system is incredible and the sense of scale is brilliant. You think your ship is bigger than that mountain???? Go and land on it and I promise you will swallow your previous statement!!!This game is worth the money. It is brilliant to see a dev who cares for his game and not for his wallet. If you have the money spare then please support Rodina!!"
