,Recommended,314230,12029207,"Posted: 8 September, 2014",all,Xaeroxe,"I really enjoyed my time with this game, it's a good concept, still needs some more fine tuning though.  The framerate gets really choppy when trying to load new enemies or regions, so that could be optimized.  I'd suggest initializing the load sooner and making sure the framerate doesn't drop under 60 FPS while loading.  The programmer art in this game is out of hand, also the user interface feels too quiet and spends too long on some text effects, particularly at the beginning of the game when choosing a name.  I would suggest animating actual visuals more than text, and having sound effects alongside those animations.  This game could really benefit from some modifications that would allow for multiplayer.  Ship layout customization feels empty, as it seems most of the objects available have no purpose.  Planetary exploration still feels kind of drifty, mostly due to a lack of view bobbing and footstep sounds.  I never feel like I'm really on another planet, just another moon.  Feels fine on asteroids and small objects, but planets should feel more solid.  Planetary entry feels unnecessarily difficult.  For the love of gosh please add some distance numbers onto the navigation icons, not having those makes the Limna drive feel crazy unwieldy, I never know when I should come out of warp.  I think the player should be able to let go of the controls whenever they want, it doesn't make sense that I have to land before I can put out a fire on my ship.  On that note, a cruise control would be great, and specifically one that can stay on even when I'm away from the controls.  Fires spread so fast that even when going at it with 2 or 3 fire extinguishers I have no hope of being able to put one out.  Some type of prologue showing the destruction of the vanguard would be cool.  A basic controls and abilities tutorial would have helped me out a lot in the early game.  Also for the demo version I'd recommend at least allowing players to load auto saves for the character they are currently playing, I had to scrap a save in the demo version because my ship was on fire and my game decided to save when the ship was at 5 hp, so there was no possible way for me to recover that ship.  It would also be nice to at some point encounter AI controlled allies, and also some of the more important dialogs should have voiceovers, so that you don't feel quite so alone in the universe despite having all this communication you're reading and reviewing.  Please make the player ship model have more than 12 polygons.  It's really ugly.  Great game though!  I love the concept and have been having a lot of fun with it.  I'm a game developer working on a similar title and I've enjoyed the opportunity to see what is and isn't working for this game.  Great job!  I look forward to future updates."
