76561198079696676,Recommended,314230,34799911,Posted: 7 September,all,agm.wallace,"Rodina is a vast and enjoyable space exploration game that incorporates an awesome sense of scale and setting into a great experience. The space combat section of the game is generally pleasing to play and I found shooting down Xeno aliens rather satisfying, however the first person combat on the surface of planets can be a little clunky at times. But, I have faith this will be smoothed out in upcoming releases. Rodina is an intensely atmospheric game and the music score is brilliant, giving a sense of a heroic space rogue. I was enchanted by the sudden atmospheric change, especially in the game's score as I came across the planet Morena for the first time, and this only become more magical as I decended to it's surface, accompanied by the soundtrack. The planet's themselves, despite the game's retro style graphics are absolutely huge and lose no detail in the process, with winding canyons, plains and mountains included. Even a terrain glitch I found looked majestic. In all a great space exploration game that should get more attention and I am excited for it's potential in the future, what this already strong game could turn into after early access. Definitely a good buy."
